1
00:01:14,708 --> 00:01:17,708
[epic orchestral music playing]

2
00:01:51,166 --> 00:01:52,541
[swooshes]

3
00:02:00,458 --> 00:02:02,791
[swooshing]

4
00:02:04,208 --> 00:02:05,791
[man] I'm not your average guy.

5
00:02:06,333 --> 00:02:08,208
I handle pressure better than most.

6
00:02:08,291 --> 00:02:11,041
Yeah, my parents are dead,
and I don't have any friends,

7
00:02:11,125 --> 00:02:13,833
but God gives everyone a challenge, right?

8
00:02:15,416 --> 00:02:18,333
I'm smart, talented, hard working.

9
00:02:18,916 --> 00:02:21,291
Success should be just around the corner.

10
00:02:21,791 --> 00:02:23,500
But I have this problem.

11
00:02:23,583 --> 00:02:24,666
I…

12
00:02:25,458 --> 00:02:27,500
I haven't been able to sleep in months.

13
00:02:29,541 --> 00:02:32,166
[tense music playing]

14
00:02:32,250 --> 00:02:34,041
[clamoring]

15
00:02:34,125 --> 00:02:35,625
[screaming]

16
00:02:36,291 --> 00:02:38,708
[clamoring continues]

17
00:02:41,125 --> 00:02:43,041
[screaming]

18
00:02:47,416 --> 00:02:48,416
[grunts]

19
00:02:50,250 --> 00:02:52,125
[sinister music plays]

20
00:02:54,875 --> 00:02:55,916
[grunts]

21
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,833
[clamoring continues]

22
00:03:03,666 --> 00:03:05,833
[sinister music continues]

23
00:03:05,916 --> 00:03:07,458
[groaning]

24
00:03:08,458 --> 00:03:11,916
[screams]

25
00:03:15,250 --> 00:03:16,541
[groans]

26
00:03:16,625 --> 00:03:19,875
[panting]

27
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:31,458
[somber music plays]

28
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:00,750
[banging on door]

29
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:03,916
[lighter clicks]

30
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,041
[banging continues]

31
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:13,500
[coughing]

32
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:16,875
[coughing continues]

33
00:04:16,958 --> 00:04:17,958
[banging on door]

34
00:04:18,041 --> 00:04:18,916
[landlord] Hey!

35
00:04:19,416 --> 00:04:22,875
Hey, I know you're in there!
Open the door or I'll break it down.

36
00:04:22,958 --> 00:04:24,750
You're gonna hide from me, huh?

37
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:26,916
I've now grown impatient with you.

38
00:04:27,416 --> 00:04:29,916
You artists are such freaks or just…
Well, I've had it!

39
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,791
Come out now! I have leftovers. 

40
00:04:32,875 --> 00:04:35,500
Eat them, get out! Don't you dare
starve to death in my house!

41
00:04:35,583 --> 00:04:37,041
-[banging]
-Open this door!

42
00:04:38,375 --> 00:04:39,250
Come on, open up!

43
00:04:40,041 --> 00:04:41,041
Open up!

44
00:04:41,625 --> 00:04:42,750
[man 1] Watch it!

45
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:44,291
[professor] What are dreams?

46
00:04:44,375 --> 00:04:47,125
Some believe that dreams
are a kind of reality

47
00:04:47,208 --> 00:04:49,625
that the soul encounters
when it leaves the body.

48
00:04:49,708 --> 00:04:51,125
From that perspective,

49
00:04:51,208 --> 00:04:53,958
our world is the true dream.
One out of many.

50
00:04:54,041 --> 00:04:57,166
[shaman] You dream of someone
chasing you to collect a debt.

51
00:04:57,250 --> 00:04:58,208
When they catch you,

52
00:04:58,291 --> 00:05:00,416
-you pay with your life.
-[professor] In fact, 

53
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:02,458
Sigmund Freud and Carl Jung

54
00:05:02,541 --> 00:05:05,750
reached similar conclusions
as China's own Duke of Zhou.

55
00:05:05,833 --> 00:05:07,083
[woman] This earth is a cage

56
00:05:07,166 --> 00:05:10,208
that humans have been locked in
by a more advanced species.

57
00:05:10,291 --> 00:05:12,000
They feared our intelligence.

58
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:15,750
We all have great wisdom and power
hidden deep within us.

59
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:17,333
Once we unlock it,

60
00:05:17,416 --> 00:05:19,208
humans can re-experience the past,

61
00:05:19,291 --> 00:05:20,416
change the future.

62
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:21,625
Become omnipotent.

63
00:05:21,708 --> 00:05:25,208
That's why our jailers only allow us
to develop 10 to 15%

64
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:26,833
of our brain capacity.

65
00:05:26,916 --> 00:05:28,958
The rest is off-limits.

66
00:05:29,041 --> 00:05:31,625
In every brain, they have placed
a horrible monster

67
00:05:31,708 --> 00:05:34,125
to make sure we never access
our true power.

68
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:36,000
punishing intruders with no mercy.

69
00:05:36,083 --> 00:05:40,125
How can we reach our power
with the enemy lying in our nightmares?

70
00:05:40,208 --> 00:05:43,291
[shaman] These charms can help you
ward off bad experience.

71
00:05:44,666 --> 00:05:47,250
[thumping]

72
00:05:47,333 --> 00:05:49,875
These practices have been
passed down by our ancestors.

73
00:05:49,958 --> 00:05:51,916
You can believe in it, or not.

74
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,041
Like all of us,
your fate has already been written.

75
00:05:56,291 --> 00:05:59,791
[professor] According to Jung,
dreams are the path to the subconscious.

76
00:06:00,375 --> 00:06:03,583
Only in dreams can people go
into the darkest corners of their minds

77
00:06:03,666 --> 00:06:05,625
and see their true selves.

78
00:06:05,708 --> 00:06:08,083
Often what they find, scares them.

79
00:06:08,166 --> 00:06:10,125
[woman] What is schizophrenics?

80
00:06:10,708 --> 00:06:13,333
It's someone who's seen
what is not supposed to.

81
00:06:13,416 --> 00:06:16,666
[atmospheric music playing]

82
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:23,458
Excuse me.

83
00:06:23,541 --> 00:06:24,541
One, please.

84
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:28,916
[sizzling]

85
00:06:29,541 --> 00:06:30,500
[gasps]

86
00:06:35,916 --> 00:06:37,125
And no egg.

87
00:06:47,125 --> 00:06:51,125
[gentle music playing]

88
00:06:58,583 --> 00:07:03,958
♪ The drizzling rain with soft wind
Leaning onto the street at dusk ♪

89
00:07:04,458 --> 00:07:09,750
♪ With the wind still slapping my face
With rain no longer blurring my eyes ♪

90
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:12,583
♪ I looked up to the lonely street light ♪

91
00:07:12,666 --> 00:07:15,541
♪ Where a sad love story came to my mind ♪

92
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:19,583
♪ I like you ♪

93
00:07:20,416 --> 00:07:22,666
♪ I like your breathtaking eyes ♪

94
00:07:23,208 --> 00:07:25,541
♪ I like your delightful laughter ♪

95
00:07:26,125 --> 00:07:28,666
♪ Just like yesterday ♪

96
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:31,083
-[tapping]
-♪ You and me ♪

97
00:07:31,166 --> 00:07:32,541
Hey, I said no eggs.

98
00:07:34,291 --> 00:07:35,291
It's on me.

99
00:07:37,666 --> 00:07:38,583
[chuckles softly]

100
00:07:40,958 --> 00:07:42,000
There you are.

101
00:07:42,083 --> 00:07:43,041
Thank you.

102
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:58,791
Why aren't you answering my calls, huh?

103
00:07:58,875 --> 00:08:00,750
-Are you pushing me?
-I'm not pushing.

104
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:02,666
-We're gonna talk now.
-I'll get back to you.

105
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:05,125
-Give me two days!
-Why are you running? Stop!

106
00:08:05,833 --> 00:08:06,791
Get back here!

107
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:08,541
[grunts]

108
00:08:08,625 --> 00:08:11,291
[lively beat plays]

109
00:08:11,375 --> 00:08:13,375
[panting]

110
00:08:15,208 --> 00:08:16,125
[groans]

111
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,083
[pants]

112
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:28,750
[sighs]

113
00:08:31,541 --> 00:08:32,375
[retching]

114
00:08:32,458 --> 00:08:33,625
[slurping loudly]

115
00:08:37,666 --> 00:08:38,916
[slurping continues]

116
00:08:41,458 --> 00:08:43,333
You really let me down, man.

117
00:08:43,916 --> 00:08:45,333
You broke our contract.

118
00:08:46,416 --> 00:08:47,750
I can sue you,

119
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:48,875
you want that?

120
00:08:48,958 --> 00:08:51,750
[Sang Yu] San,
I something very serious to tell you.

121
00:08:58,375 --> 00:08:59,333
This bowl

122
00:09:00,166 --> 00:09:01,250
represents the human mind.

123
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:03,541
There's a fish moving around

124
00:09:03,625 --> 00:09:05,166
that represent your consciousness.

125
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:07,583
The rest of the water, which is empty,

126
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:09,083
represents the subconscious.

127
00:09:09,666 --> 00:09:12,125
[slurping]

128
00:09:15,375 --> 00:09:17,708
When conscious mind
leaves the subconscious behind,

129
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:19,708
it's like a fish out of water.

130
00:09:19,791 --> 00:09:21,458
I'm just like this fish.

131
00:09:21,541 --> 00:09:23,916
-I'm dying here.
-[waitress] Enjoy your noodles.

132
00:09:26,958 --> 00:09:28,375
Hey! Don't touch that!

133
00:09:30,750 --> 00:09:33,666
Wait. Are you telling me this is all
because of your insomnia?

134
00:09:34,708 --> 00:09:36,833
When I try to sleep,
my nightmares find me.

135
00:09:37,916 --> 00:09:40,250
At first,
I even thought I was schizophrenic.

136
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:41,458
Or maybe cursed.

137
00:09:42,416 --> 00:09:45,083
-It's something else.
-If you can't sleep, then write!

138
00:09:45,166 --> 00:09:47,208
I can't barely concentrate on it.

139
00:09:47,291 --> 00:09:49,333
Then give me back the advance.

140
00:09:51,166 --> 00:09:52,125
I spent it already.

141
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:54,500
Spend it on what?

142
00:09:55,125 --> 00:09:56,750
I think you're just lazy!

143
00:09:56,833 --> 00:10:00,041
You don't even try to work,
you keep making excuses.

144
00:10:00,791 --> 00:10:02,500
I'll give you ten more days.

145
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,625
Do you think your writing is so special?

146
00:10:05,208 --> 00:10:08,250
I took a big risk
when I hired you to write this.

147
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:10,833
It should be easy money for you!

148
00:10:10,916 --> 00:10:13,166
So, whatever you need to do, do it!

149
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:15,000
Just please make it quick.

150
00:10:15,083 --> 00:10:16,583
Pull yourself together!

151
00:10:21,875 --> 00:10:24,875
[gloomy music]

152
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:49,833
[rattles]

153
00:10:57,958 --> 00:10:59,333
[grunting]

154
00:11:00,125 --> 00:11:02,125
[groaning]

155
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:08,458
[somber music]

156
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:20,333
[thuds]

157
00:11:23,708 --> 00:11:26,166
-[woman] I'm done.
-[man] Let's get of here.

158
00:11:26,791 --> 00:11:27,750
Come again.

159
00:11:30,916 --> 00:11:33,958
[stomach growling]

160
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:41,291
[stomach growls]

161
00:11:45,750 --> 00:11:47,208
[yawning]

162
00:11:56,416 --> 00:11:58,208
[keyboard clacking]

163
00:12:00,916 --> 00:12:02,250
[stomach growls]

164
00:12:04,375 --> 00:12:06,458
[whooshing]

165
00:12:08,625 --> 00:12:11,375
[ominous music]

166
00:12:12,416 --> 00:12:15,416
[footsteps thumping]

167
00:12:22,708 --> 00:12:24,375
[grunting]

168
00:12:26,208 --> 00:12:27,708
[choking]

169
00:12:30,625 --> 00:12:32,625
[thudding]

170
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:36,916
[exhales]

171
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:40,083
[sighs]

172
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:10,833
[reflecting music playing]

173
00:13:12,916 --> 00:13:14,000
[Sang Yu] San,

174
00:13:14,583 --> 00:13:15,541
I'm sorry.

175
00:13:15,625 --> 00:13:17,208
I can't write the script.

176
00:13:18,375 --> 00:13:21,291
I guess I'll have to pay you back
in the next life.

177
00:13:24,083 --> 00:13:26,041
I can't keep going like this.

178
00:13:26,791 --> 00:13:28,458
If I can't fight the nightmares,

179
00:13:29,666 --> 00:13:32,250
then I'll never be able to face
the reality there.

180
00:13:35,166 --> 00:13:38,291
I don't think I can tell
the difference anymore between reality

181
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:40,208
and my dreams.

182
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:42,291
This feeling,

183
00:13:43,083 --> 00:13:44,916
it's too much to handle.

184
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,291
[emotional music playing]

185
00:13:46,375 --> 00:13:47,625
Everything I ever wanted

186
00:13:48,458 --> 00:13:50,166
is getting further away from me.

187
00:13:53,708 --> 00:13:55,458
My life doesn't mean anything.

188
00:13:55,541 --> 00:13:56,875
Not anymore.

189
00:13:58,416 --> 00:14:00,125
I wanna see my friends again.

190
00:14:00,916 --> 00:14:02,416
Say goodbye.

191
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:04,666
[vendor] Hey! Want some breakfast?

192
00:14:16,333 --> 00:14:19,250
This time with egg and sausage!
On the house!

193
00:14:19,333 --> 00:14:20,875
[sobbing]

194
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:31,500
[emotional music rising]

195
00:14:31,583 --> 00:14:33,458
[whimpers]

196
00:14:44,833 --> 00:14:45,916
Tastes so good…

197
00:14:51,083 --> 00:14:52,708
I definitely owe you for this,

198
00:14:53,250 --> 00:14:54,708
but I'm afraid I can't pay you back.

199
00:14:55,375 --> 00:14:57,583
We all hit a rough spot now and then.

200
00:14:59,041 --> 00:15:00,791
Nothing we can't beat, huh?

201
00:15:00,875 --> 00:15:03,458
I must have done
something horrible in my past life,

202
00:15:04,166 --> 00:15:06,250
I think I'm paying for it in this one.

203
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:07,583
Paying day and night.

204
00:15:07,666 --> 00:15:09,541
I'm paying all the time!

205
00:15:10,375 --> 00:15:12,958
Come on, what are you talking about?
[chuckles]

206
00:15:13,791 --> 00:15:15,166
What was so bad, young man?

207
00:15:16,875 --> 00:15:17,708
Breakup?

208
00:15:19,541 --> 00:15:20,583
You were fired?

209
00:15:21,791 --> 00:15:22,750
Insulted?

210
00:15:23,875 --> 00:15:25,500
[laughs]

211
00:15:29,416 --> 00:15:31,625
None of those things owed your life.

212
00:15:32,375 --> 00:15:36,041
I used my life every night
in my nightmares, it is horrible.

213
00:15:36,125 --> 00:15:40,166
I can't sleep anymore because of it.
How do you expect me to deal with that?

214
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:45,916
How about next time you dream,
just wake up before you die?

215
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:48,291
[atmospheric music plays]

216
00:15:48,375 --> 00:15:49,458
How will I do that?

217
00:15:50,083 --> 00:15:51,791
Face it, I'm hopeless.

218
00:15:52,458 --> 00:15:53,541
[sniffles]

219
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,541
You know,

220
00:15:56,625 --> 00:15:58,583
it's strange that people wish to die.

221
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,333
They always say,

222
00:16:00,416 --> 00:16:02,291
"I'm better off dead."

223
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:06,333
Then they keep on living
just the same, don't they?

224
00:16:06,416 --> 00:16:09,541
[gentle music playing]

225
00:16:09,625 --> 00:16:10,708
So, you see,

226
00:16:11,583 --> 00:16:12,833
wishing for death

227
00:16:13,583 --> 00:16:15,625
reminds us that we're still alive.

228
00:16:15,708 --> 00:16:17,041
By the same logic,

229
00:16:17,833 --> 00:16:19,375
if you wanna wake up,

230
00:16:19,458 --> 00:16:20,791
just say,

231
00:16:21,875 --> 00:16:23,625
"I'm only dreaming."

232
00:16:25,125 --> 00:16:26,833
And you just might wake up.

233
00:16:28,416 --> 00:16:30,000
[chuckles]

234
00:16:30,083 --> 00:16:32,458
[both laughing]

235
00:16:45,541 --> 00:16:47,916
[delicate music plays]

236
00:17:08,458 --> 00:17:09,458
In this condition,

237
00:17:09,541 --> 00:17:10,750
I'm gonna give you 20.

238
00:18:12,083 --> 00:18:13,208
[woman] Sang Yu?

239
00:18:16,041 --> 00:18:17,000
Is that really you?

240
00:18:19,958 --> 00:18:21,250
What happened?

241
00:18:23,541 --> 00:18:24,750
Do you need some help?

242
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:30,041
But don't you don't remember me at all?

243
00:18:33,083 --> 00:18:34,041
Come on.

244
00:18:34,125 --> 00:18:35,750
Let's go get something to eat.

245
00:18:39,250 --> 00:18:40,250
It's okay.

246
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:43,500
[cracking]

247
00:18:44,541 --> 00:18:45,875
[gasps]

248
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:47,125
[groaning]

249
00:18:49,666 --> 00:18:50,500
[bang on window]

250
00:18:50,583 --> 00:18:53,666
[tense music playing]

251
00:18:54,375 --> 00:18:55,541
[gasping]

252
00:18:55,625 --> 00:18:58,791
Hello? Ambulance here right away.

253
00:19:00,416 --> 00:19:01,250
[gasps]

254
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:03,500
[gasps]

255
00:19:03,583 --> 00:19:05,750
[grunting]

256
00:19:08,416 --> 00:19:10,000
[squelching]

257
00:19:12,416 --> 00:19:14,458
[vendor] If you wanna wake up, just say,

258
00:19:14,541 --> 00:19:16,041
"I'm only dreaming."

259
00:19:16,125 --> 00:19:17,166
I'm only dreaming.

260
00:19:17,250 --> 00:19:18,208
[groans]

261
00:19:18,916 --> 00:19:21,916
[intense choral music plays]

262
00:19:31,791 --> 00:19:33,708
[groaning]

263
00:19:33,791 --> 00:19:36,041
[panting]

264
00:19:38,791 --> 00:19:40,875
[warbling]

265
00:19:49,166 --> 00:19:50,041
-[thumps]
-[gasps]

266
00:19:54,750 --> 00:19:57,125
[mysterious music plays]

267
00:20:03,291 --> 00:20:05,166
[panting]

268
00:20:19,875 --> 00:20:20,833
Ow.

269
00:20:21,833 --> 00:20:24,625
[mysterious music continues]

270
00:20:30,666 --> 00:20:32,125
-[clanks]
-[gasps]

271
00:20:36,583 --> 00:20:37,958
This is all a dream!

272
00:20:40,833 --> 00:20:43,333
I said I'm dreaming! I'm dreaming!

273
00:20:45,125 --> 00:20:48,125
