556
00:43:18,666 --> 00:43:20,291
Oh, wow!

557
00:43:22,750 --> 00:43:24,583
[San] I just fell asleep.

558
00:43:24,666 --> 00:43:26,500
-It's still hot, careful.
-Thank you.

559
00:43:26,583 --> 00:43:27,458
[gasps softly]

560
00:43:28,250 --> 00:43:30,291
Wow, seems our tables are full.

561
00:43:30,375 --> 00:43:31,500
Mm, I'll get it to go.

562
00:43:33,041 --> 00:43:34,583
[man] I want an Americano.

563
00:43:36,958 --> 00:43:38,166
[Hua'er] Here you go.

564
00:43:40,083 --> 00:43:41,875
I'll… I'll be with you in a second.

565
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:46,458
I'm sorry, we're really busy today.
There you are.

566
00:43:51,250 --> 00:43:54,250
[machine whirring]

567
00:44:00,291 --> 00:44:02,916
[atmospheric music playing]

568
00:44:08,708 --> 00:44:11,208
Come on, people.
I'm literally handing out money.

569
00:44:11,291 --> 00:44:14,166
-You got a crazy business model, man.
-Give me some more.

570
00:44:14,250 --> 00:44:15,958
All right, go on. Get in there.

571
00:44:22,041 --> 00:44:23,250
Thank you.

572
00:44:36,250 --> 00:44:37,875
[locking]

573
00:44:37,958 --> 00:44:39,083
[sighs]

574
00:44:42,375 --> 00:44:43,375
Mm.

575
00:44:46,666 --> 00:44:49,958
All those people in my shop…
I mean, our shop.

576
00:44:50,541 --> 00:44:52,958
I've never seen anything like it before.

577
00:44:53,708 --> 00:44:55,833
You must be my lucky charm.

578
00:44:55,916 --> 00:44:57,208
No, no.

579
00:44:58,625 --> 00:45:01,000
I've never had so much coffee before.

580
00:45:01,083 --> 00:45:02,250
Five cups, I think.

581
00:45:02,916 --> 00:45:03,791
It was six cups.

582
00:45:03,875 --> 00:45:05,458
Ah, six cups?

583
00:45:05,541 --> 00:45:07,250
[both chuckle]

584
00:45:09,416 --> 00:45:12,125
Hey, I've never actually seen you
go into work.

585
00:45:13,041 --> 00:45:15,458
Mm, I usually do my work at night.

586
00:45:15,541 --> 00:45:16,583
Ah.

587
00:45:16,666 --> 00:45:17,750
Night shift?

588
00:45:18,291 --> 00:45:20,250
[both chuckle]

589
00:45:22,083 --> 00:45:24,500
All right, you give me three good hints,

590
00:45:24,583 --> 00:45:27,291
then I'll guess what you do for a living.

591
00:45:27,375 --> 00:45:29,458
-You won't be able to.
-Come on, try me.

592
00:45:29,541 --> 00:45:31,166
I think I'm going to get it.

593
00:45:31,250 --> 00:45:34,166
[gentle music playing]

594
00:45:35,458 --> 00:45:36,666
Dreaming.

595
00:45:36,750 --> 00:45:37,750
Seeking.

596
00:45:38,291 --> 00:45:39,125
Gaining.

597
00:45:42,708 --> 00:45:45,000
[Hua'er] I've got it.
You're a screenwriter.

598
00:45:46,833 --> 00:45:47,916
So, I was right?

599
00:45:48,000 --> 00:45:49,916
How could you have guessed that?

600
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:51,791
Well, if you think about it,

601
00:45:51,875 --> 00:45:53,250
the story is like a dream.

602
00:45:53,833 --> 00:45:55,666
And the second hint, seeking.

603
00:45:55,750 --> 00:45:59,791
The characters, always looking for love
or looking for themselves.

604
00:45:59,875 --> 00:46:03,666
As for the gaining, people always expect
to gain something at the end of a story.

605
00:46:03,750 --> 00:46:05,375
Maybe that would be success

606
00:46:05,458 --> 00:46:07,375
or an adventure at the very least.

607
00:46:07,458 --> 00:46:08,541
[both chuckle]

608
00:46:24,041 --> 00:46:25,208
[chuckles]

609
00:46:30,083 --> 00:46:30,958
[clears throat]

610
00:46:32,083 --> 00:46:34,958
[rock music]

611
00:46:35,041 --> 00:46:36,708
[hooting]

612
00:46:38,625 --> 00:46:39,666
[tires screech]

613
00:46:42,875 --> 00:46:44,291
[whooshing]

614
00:46:45,500 --> 00:46:46,416
[grunts]

615
00:46:54,250 --> 00:46:56,833
[laughing]

616
00:46:56,916 --> 00:46:57,750
I'm dreaming!

617
00:47:01,833 --> 00:47:03,666
Who's there? What's going on?

618
00:47:03,750 --> 00:47:05,083
What's happening?

619
00:47:07,791 --> 00:47:09,291
[laughs]

620
00:47:10,875 --> 00:47:11,958
Thank you.

621
00:47:18,125 --> 00:47:19,541
I guess you're planning

622
00:47:19,625 --> 00:47:21,291
to walk me home every day?

623
00:47:22,125 --> 00:47:23,041
[scoffs]

624
00:47:24,125 --> 00:47:25,208
If you don't mind.

625
00:47:26,208 --> 00:47:29,083
Since you're my partner,
it's the least I can do for you.

626
00:47:29,166 --> 00:47:32,250
To be fair,
you also buy six coffees every day.

627
00:47:33,333 --> 00:47:34,500
[Sang Yu clears throat]

628
00:47:36,750 --> 00:47:39,250
[car beeps]

629
00:47:40,083 --> 00:47:41,541
-This is your car?
-[chuckles]

630
00:47:41,625 --> 00:47:42,625
Give it a shot.

631
00:47:42,708 --> 00:47:44,375
I haven't driven in so long.

632
00:47:44,958 --> 00:47:47,333
Go ahead. You can crash it if you want.

633
00:47:47,416 --> 00:47:50,083
What? No way!
I could never afford to fix this.

634
00:47:52,875 --> 00:47:54,125
[car revs]

635
00:47:54,708 --> 00:47:55,541
[Hua'er sighs]

636
00:47:56,375 --> 00:47:57,708
-It's fast.
-I see that.

637
00:47:57,791 --> 00:47:58,750
Give me a sec.

638
00:48:04,541 --> 00:48:07,875
[gentle music playing]

639
00:48:12,458 --> 00:48:13,625
Ah, you know,

640
00:48:14,875 --> 00:48:16,375
I got this car for you.

641
00:48:22,000 --> 00:48:24,041
Okay, you must be super rich.

642
00:48:28,000 --> 00:48:30,958
Then I guess
you're a very famous screenwriter.

643
00:48:31,041 --> 00:48:33,958
Why don't we pretend
I'm one of your characters?

644
00:48:34,958 --> 00:48:37,500
Do you want me to act sweet or assertive?

645
00:48:38,041 --> 00:48:39,250
How about sweet?

646
00:48:44,583 --> 00:48:46,416
I've been single for a while,

647
00:48:47,833 --> 00:48:51,791
but it's not because I was holding out
for a car, a mansion, or anything else.

648
00:48:54,125 --> 00:48:55,958
Hey, how rich are you?

649
00:48:56,041 --> 00:48:56,875
You can tell me.

650
00:48:56,958 --> 00:48:58,541
[chuckles]

651
00:49:02,375 --> 00:49:05,291
[gentle pop music in Chinese plays]

652
00:49:07,083 --> 00:49:09,416
No, you don't get it.
Trust me, you'll love it.

653
00:49:09,500 --> 00:49:11,458
-I've never been inside this.
-Trust me.

654
00:49:12,208 --> 00:49:14,833
Are you seriously still wearing
your school uniform?

655
00:49:14,916 --> 00:49:16,291
Can you believe this guy?

656
00:49:16,375 --> 00:49:18,958
♪ I looked up to the lonely street light ♪

657
00:49:19,041 --> 00:49:22,333
♪ Where a sad love story came to my mind ♪

658
00:49:24,000 --> 00:49:26,750
♪ I like you ♪

659
00:49:26,833 --> 00:49:29,416
♪ I like your breathtaking eyes ♪

660
00:49:29,500 --> 00:49:32,708
♪ I like your delightful laughter ♪

661
00:49:32,791 --> 00:49:35,333
♪ I wish ♪

662
00:49:35,416 --> 00:49:38,458
♪ To gently caress ♪

663
00:49:38,541 --> 00:49:41,416
♪ Your lovely face again ♪

664
00:49:41,500 --> 00:49:44,083
♪ To hold hands and talk in our dreams ♪

665
00:49:44,166 --> 00:49:47,458
♪ Just like yesterday ♪

666
00:49:47,541 --> 00:49:49,333
♪ You and me ♪

667
00:49:49,416 --> 00:49:50,416
Who are you?

668
00:49:51,083 --> 00:49:52,250
Sang Yu.

669
00:49:52,333 --> 00:49:56,083
♪ Every night, I walk with my shadow ♪

670
00:49:56,166 --> 00:49:58,708
♪ Wandering around ♪

671
00:49:58,791 --> 00:50:01,625
♪ Feeling so cold ♪

672
00:50:01,708 --> 00:50:04,125
[Hua'er] What are you looking at?
Get out of here.

673
00:50:04,208 --> 00:50:05,208
[sobbing]

674
00:50:05,291 --> 00:50:07,916
♪ I used to live in my own world ♪

675
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:10,666
♪ Without ever knowing ♪

676
00:50:10,750 --> 00:50:13,750
♪ His pain ♪

677
00:50:13,833 --> 00:50:16,958
[crying]

678
00:50:19,750 --> 00:50:22,291
♪ I like you ♪

679
00:50:22,375 --> 00:50:25,041
♪ I like your breathtaking eyes ♪

680
00:50:25,125 --> 00:50:28,083
♪ I like your delightful laughter ♪

681
00:50:28,166 --> 00:50:31,208
♪ I wish ♪

682
00:50:31,291 --> 00:50:34,083
♪ To gently caress ♪

683
00:50:34,166 --> 00:50:36,916
♪ Your lovely face again ♪

684
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:39,750
♪ To hold hands and talk in our dreams ♪

685
00:50:39,833 --> 00:50:43,083
♪ Just like yesterday ♪

686
00:50:43,166 --> 00:50:47,041
♪ You and me ♪

687
00:50:58,375 --> 00:51:01,541
We should go and see one of the movies
that you've written, huh?

688
00:51:04,916 --> 00:51:06,500
Wouldn't that be a good idea?

689
00:51:07,166 --> 00:51:09,000
I wanna see a story you've written.

690
00:51:10,958 --> 00:51:12,708
[both chuckle]

691
00:51:20,416 --> 00:51:23,208
[keyboard clacking]

692
00:51:23,291 --> 00:51:26,416
[dramatic music]

693
00:51:32,666 --> 00:51:33,958
A mocha, please.

694
00:51:44,458 --> 00:51:46,416
Hey, what's going on?

695
00:51:47,291 --> 00:51:49,708
I thought you didn't need
to write these anymore.

696
00:51:55,166 --> 00:51:56,416
[sighs]

697
00:52:00,833 --> 00:52:03,208
[Hua'er] Why don't we pretend
I'm one of your characters.

698
00:52:03,291 --> 00:52:05,833
Do you want me to act sweet or assertive?

699
00:52:05,916 --> 00:52:09,500
-[Sang Yu] Assertive, I can take it.
-[Hua'er] You should know,

700
00:52:09,583 --> 00:52:11,750
I usually dump three guys like you
every year.

701
00:52:13,208 --> 00:52:16,500
[ominous music]

702
00:52:45,666 --> 00:52:48,458
[crackling]

703
00:52:49,208 --> 00:52:50,333
I'm dreaming!

704
00:52:52,625 --> 00:52:53,875
[whimpers]

705
00:52:57,000 --> 00:52:58,541
[San] This is amazing, yeah?

706
00:53:00,125 --> 00:53:01,333
[gasps]

707
00:53:01,416 --> 00:53:03,041
What's in your hand?

708
00:53:04,375 --> 00:53:05,500
So, you read the script?

709
00:53:07,250 --> 00:53:10,083
Did you find this story
in your dream as well? [sniffles]

710
00:53:10,625 --> 00:53:11,833
It's wonderful!

711
00:53:11,916 --> 00:53:13,125
So touching!

712
00:53:13,208 --> 00:53:15,416
[announcer 1] Who wrote this?
This is gonna be a hit!

713
00:53:15,500 --> 00:53:16,750
I'll make 200,000!

714
00:53:16,833 --> 00:53:19,416
Only 200,000? That's funny.

715
00:53:19,500 --> 00:53:21,708
The screenwriter doesn't want money.

716
00:53:21,791 --> 00:53:25,625
But he wants it done right. That means
big stars for the romantic leads.

717
00:53:25,708 --> 00:53:28,375
-[man] San.
-I want double this time.

718
00:53:29,083 --> 00:53:31,333
Are you serious?
I'm only putting in five million.

719
00:53:31,416 --> 00:53:32,625
I can't afford it.

720
00:53:33,208 --> 00:53:34,541
What if I invest?

721
00:53:35,333 --> 00:53:37,083
A hundred million.

722
00:53:38,666 --> 00:53:39,833
[announcer] Sang Yu,

723
00:53:39,916 --> 00:53:43,166
for many years, a promising young writer,

724
00:53:43,250 --> 00:53:46,375
he is now in the middle
of an unprecedented wave of success

725
00:53:46,458 --> 00:53:49,625
by being recognized as one of China's
most important filmmakers.

726
00:53:49,708 --> 00:53:51,666
A once in a generation visionary,

727
00:53:51,750 --> 00:53:54,041
he's become a major player
in the industry.

728
00:53:54,125 --> 00:53:56,541
[San] If you're not interested,
I can find someone else.

729
00:53:56,625 --> 00:53:58,083
I have other buyers.

730
00:53:58,166 --> 00:54:00,416
For one,
I could sell it right at the price

731
00:54:00,500 --> 00:54:03,416
and force you to pay
ten times more to get it.

732
00:54:03,500 --> 00:54:06,833
[announcer] An avid reader
by the age of three, a poet by five,

733
00:54:06,916 --> 00:54:07,916
a producer at seven.

734
00:54:08,000 --> 00:54:11,250
He's been called
the Shakespeare of Chinese Cinema.

735
00:54:11,333 --> 00:54:14,916
Already on the industry's radar
during his college years,

736
00:54:15,000 --> 00:54:16,958
Sang Yu kept a low profile

737
00:54:17,041 --> 00:54:19,625
working behind the scenes
with top directors.

738
00:54:21,166 --> 00:54:22,625
Sure, let's do it.

739
00:54:22,708 --> 00:54:24,541
[San] We'll get the contract ready

740
00:54:24,625 --> 00:54:26,958
and expect the first payment tomorrow.

741
00:54:31,416 --> 00:54:34,291
[announcer] Despite being offered
an easy act of fame,

742
00:54:34,375 --> 00:54:35,583
he chose to reject it.

743
00:54:35,666 --> 00:54:39,416
Instead, he focused on living
a fulfilling and simple life.

744
00:54:39,500 --> 00:54:42,125
So he gave up ownership of all his work

745
00:54:42,208 --> 00:54:45,250
and refused to participate
in media coverage.

746
00:54:45,916 --> 00:54:47,958
Since then, he's traveled the world,

747
00:54:48,041 --> 00:54:50,666
collecting thousands of stories
and honing his voice.

748
00:54:50,750 --> 00:54:55,291
This year, he has over 20
top film projects set to begin production.

749
00:54:55,375 --> 00:54:57,958
If think of Sang Yu
as a big shot in the business…

750
00:54:58,041 --> 00:55:01,250
-Isn't this a little exaggerated?
-Fake it 'till you make it, bro.

751
00:55:01,333 --> 00:55:04,375
[applause]

752
00:55:06,375 --> 00:55:08,291
I wanna let you know
I'm not as good as all that.

753
00:55:08,375 --> 00:55:09,958
For a long time,

754
00:55:10,041 --> 00:55:11,541
I couldn't write anything good

755
00:55:12,125 --> 00:55:14,125
because I didn't know why I was writing.

756
00:55:15,250 --> 00:55:16,583
But I think that now,

757
00:55:16,666 --> 00:55:19,958
I have found a pretty good reason.
Thanks to that reason,

758
00:55:20,041 --> 00:55:21,458
I hope I never let you down.

759
00:55:21,541 --> 00:55:22,708
Thanks again.

760
00:55:22,791 --> 00:55:25,166
[applause]

761
00:55:30,125 --> 00:55:33,416
[foreboding music]

762
00:55:43,208 --> 00:55:44,208
[inhales deeply]

763
00:55:47,125 --> 00:55:50,291
[intense music playing]

764
00:56:00,041 --> 00:56:00,875
[grunts]

765
00:56:13,125 --> 00:56:16,166
[intense music continues]

766
00:56:20,166 --> 00:56:21,166
[grunt]

767
00:56:25,583 --> 00:56:27,041
[rumbling]

768
00:57:01,125 --> 00:57:02,500
[Sang Yu] Just incredible.

769
00:57:03,000 --> 00:57:04,958
Not even Mike Tyson has one of these.

770
00:57:08,666 --> 00:57:09,916
What's on your mind?

771
00:57:15,875 --> 00:57:18,083
Lately, I've come to realize something.

772
00:57:18,166 --> 00:57:19,208
Uh-huh?

773
00:57:19,291 --> 00:57:22,250
There are two kinds of people
in this world who succeed.

774
00:57:23,166 --> 00:57:24,208
First group,

775
00:57:25,000 --> 00:57:26,166
they're traitors.

776
00:57:27,791 --> 00:57:30,958
They are willing to betray the things
that most people wouldn't.

777
00:57:31,625 --> 00:57:34,458
These people betray friendship, love,
even family.

778
00:57:35,750 --> 00:57:37,625
In exchange for their betrayal,

779
00:57:38,250 --> 00:57:40,625
they get empty rewards they call success.

780
00:57:40,708 --> 00:57:43,166
The other kind were called thieves.

781
00:57:43,958 --> 00:57:45,333
Who think they're geniuses.

782
00:57:46,208 --> 00:57:49,500
What else do you call someone
whose invention changes the world?

783
00:57:51,125 --> 00:57:53,250
But they haven't really invented anything.

784
00:57:54,750 --> 00:57:57,625
All of their inventions are discoveries.

785
00:57:59,250 --> 00:58:02,041
Made in a different reality
that exists around us.

786
00:58:02,750 --> 00:58:04,750
Usually, you can't see it or feel it,

787
00:58:05,500 --> 00:58:08,541
but if you get the opportunity
to see that world,

788
00:58:08,625 --> 00:58:10,750
perhaps take something you find back home,

789
00:58:11,541 --> 00:58:13,375
then you've really discovered something.

790
00:58:15,333 --> 00:58:18,083
-[San clears throat]
-That was the door I went through.

791
00:58:19,250 --> 00:58:20,083
[San] Oh.

792
00:58:23,041 --> 00:58:26,375
[Sang Yu] But I feel there has to be more.
Something beyond myself.

793
00:58:26,458 --> 00:58:27,291
That's it.

794
00:58:27,958 --> 00:58:29,708
I see what's happening here.

795
00:58:29,791 --> 00:58:31,791
Now, this is what God intended.

796
00:58:31,875 --> 00:58:36,125
Huh? He chose you
to use this power to help others.

797
00:58:37,666 --> 00:58:40,125
I think I'm about
to get philosophical myself.

798
00:58:40,750 --> 00:58:43,000
Throughout all of human history,

799
00:58:43,083 --> 00:58:46,541
there are few principal factors
that have been a cause of misery.

800
00:58:46,625 --> 00:58:48,708
There are natural disasters, obviously.

801
00:58:48,791 --> 00:58:50,458
and then there is war.

802
00:58:51,125 --> 00:58:54,375
So tell me, what's the main cause of war?

803
00:58:55,375 --> 00:58:56,541
Isn't it poverty?

804
00:58:57,208 --> 00:58:59,458
Therefore, if you eliminate poverty,

805
00:58:59,541 --> 00:59:01,208
you eliminate war.

806
00:59:01,291 --> 00:59:03,708
Seriously,
you could be the one who does that.

807
00:59:04,458 --> 00:59:06,333
We could build a skyscraper.

808
00:59:06,416 --> 00:59:09,041
At least twice as tall
as any in the world.

809
00:59:09,125 --> 00:59:12,416
We'll invite all the starving
and homeless people we can find.

810
00:59:12,500 --> 00:59:14,791
I'm talking refugees and pirates,
everyone.

811
00:59:14,875 --> 00:59:17,583
We give them food, shelter, education,
all free!

812
00:59:17,666 --> 00:59:19,958
We could build more buildings
on every country!

813
00:59:20,791 --> 00:59:22,041
We pull this off,

814
00:59:22,125 --> 00:59:25,625
you'll win the Nobel Peace Prize
every year!

815
00:59:25,708 --> 00:59:28,166
You say the word,
I'll get started on it now!

816
00:59:29,041 --> 00:59:31,416
We're gonna change the world together,
Sang Yu!

817
00:59:31,500 --> 00:59:35,458
[triumphant music]

818
00:59:38,375 --> 00:59:39,208
[scoffs]

819
00:59:39,916 --> 00:59:42,416
[Hua'er] I've never seen my shop
from this angle before.

820
00:59:44,333 --> 00:59:45,208
[snickers]

821
00:59:47,750 --> 00:59:48,833
Hey, look over there.

822
00:59:49,333 --> 00:59:53,041
I once used to think it didn't matter
to the city whether I existed or not

823
00:59:53,958 --> 00:59:55,750
But now, mostly because of you,

824
00:59:56,708 --> 00:59:57,750
I actually think

825
00:59:59,083 --> 01:00:01,375
I'm helping this city to shine,

826
01:00:01,458 --> 01:00:02,791
even brighter than before.

827
01:00:04,375 --> 01:00:06,625
[fireworks explode]

828
01:00:06,708 --> 01:00:10,000
[gentle music soaring]

829
01:00:11,125 --> 01:00:12,250
[gasps]

830
01:00:12,916 --> 01:00:14,000
[screams]

831
01:00:15,666 --> 01:00:17,125
[Sang Yu] These days…

832
01:00:18,625 --> 01:00:20,583
I feel truly alive.

833
01:00:22,958 --> 01:00:24,875
I never would have dreamed
I'd win you over.

834
01:00:26,000 --> 01:00:27,750
But spending these days together,

835
01:00:29,666 --> 01:00:30,958
is almost enough for me.

836
01:00:40,000 --> 01:00:41,583
How long can we make this last?

837
01:00:42,458 --> 01:00:43,333
Mm?

838
01:00:45,500 --> 01:00:47,375
From the moment you appeared,

839
01:00:48,500 --> 01:00:50,666
until the day you'll disappear?

840
01:01:05,875 --> 01:01:07,541
[Sang Yu] I'm not going anywhere.

841
01:01:15,541 --> 01:01:17,416
You probably don't remember me.

842
01:01:18,000 --> 01:01:20,041
I use to skip class

843
01:01:21,625 --> 01:01:23,458
to go to the movies with you.

844
01:01:24,291 --> 01:01:25,750
[chuckles]

845
01:01:26,958 --> 01:01:27,875
[sighs]

846
01:01:35,000 --> 01:01:36,833
If I were that same boy today,

847
01:01:40,791 --> 01:01:42,333
would you want to be with me?

848
01:01:49,041 --> 01:01:50,166
Mm…

849
01:01:51,958 --> 01:01:53,750
[sighs]

850
01:01:55,791 --> 01:01:57,958
[water running]

851
01:02:08,583 --> 01:02:09,541
[grunts]

852
01:02:09,625 --> 01:02:10,750
[coughing]

853
01:02:10,833 --> 01:02:12,500
[grunting]

854
01:02:12,583 --> 01:02:14,541
[Sang Yu groaning]

855
01:02:14,625 --> 01:02:15,583
Sang Yu?

856
01:02:15,666 --> 01:02:17,500
[panting]

857
01:02:28,625 --> 01:02:29,708
Sang Yu?

858
01:02:29,791 --> 01:02:31,000
Are you okay?

859
01:02:33,000 --> 01:02:33,958
Sang Yu?

860
01:02:41,875 --> 01:02:44,875
[somber music]

861
01:02:46,958 --> 01:02:49,375
♪ Making you love me ♪

862
01:02:49,458 --> 01:02:51,250
♪ Is simple ♪

863
01:02:51,875 --> 01:02:53,666
♪ But meeting you ♪

864
01:02:53,750 --> 01:02:55,958
♪ Is so hard ♪

865
01:02:57,416 --> 01:03:02,125
♪ You ride a boat with sails raised ♪

866
01:03:02,208 --> 01:03:06,333
♪ To the opposite shore ♪

867
01:03:06,416 --> 01:03:07,541
[elevator dings]

868
01:03:10,166 --> 01:03:14,583
♪ It's so simple for men
And women to fall in love ♪

869
01:03:14,666 --> 01:03:18,750
♪ When trapped
In their obsession with you ♪

870
01:03:20,625 --> 01:03:25,083
♪ The boat overturns ♪

871
01:03:25,583 --> 01:03:30,041
♪ And your wounds start to rot ♪

872
01:03:41,125 --> 01:03:43,500
[muffled laughter]

873
01:03:43,583 --> 01:03:45,083
Oh, Sang Yu?

874
01:03:46,625 --> 01:03:47,583
Hey.

875
01:03:49,458 --> 01:03:51,041
[chuckles] Here's the big man.

876
01:03:52,666 --> 01:03:53,500
[chuckles]

877
01:03:54,166 --> 01:03:56,375
Why are you doing
drinking in here all alone?

878
01:03:57,375 --> 01:04:00,250
Hey, why don't you come
and join us out here?

879
01:04:01,083 --> 01:04:02,916
I'll make sure you have a good time.

880
01:04:03,000 --> 01:04:03,958
I'm tired.

881
01:04:07,958 --> 01:04:10,458
You and Hua'er getting to fight
or something?

882
01:04:12,875 --> 01:04:13,958
[cellphone chimes]

883
01:04:20,375 --> 01:04:22,041
These women, right?

884
01:04:22,125 --> 01:04:25,500
-[cellphone clacking]
-After their games playing hard to get,

885
01:04:25,583 --> 01:04:28,125
suddenly, they want all your attention.

886
01:04:28,208 --> 01:04:32,500
Just when you think you found true love,
suddenly, she was interested.

887
01:04:32,583 --> 01:04:35,791
So easy to think
women are different, special,

888
01:04:35,875 --> 01:04:38,166
started to think
she doesn't want anything from you.

889
01:04:38,250 --> 01:04:40,041
-But then--
-Hey, San.

890
01:04:40,125 --> 01:04:41,041
Huh?

891
01:04:41,125 --> 01:04:42,791
You think after all we've taken,

892
01:04:43,458 --> 01:04:44,791
there might be karma?

893
01:04:45,916 --> 01:04:47,750
Well, when you took something,

894
01:04:51,708 --> 01:04:54,875
you only took what was yours.
You never stole from anyone.

895
01:04:54,958 --> 01:04:56,333
Where is the karma in that?

896
01:04:56,416 --> 01:04:58,416
You didn't fight with Hua'er, did you?

897
01:04:58,500 --> 01:05:00,958
Do you remember that door
I was telling you about?

898
01:05:02,125 --> 01:05:03,583
I'm starting to think…

899
01:05:06,541 --> 01:05:08,833
one day, I won't come back.

900
01:05:08,916 --> 01:05:09,916
What are you saying?

901
01:05:10,000 --> 01:05:12,250
That you'll got to sleep
and never wake up?

902
01:05:13,166 --> 01:05:15,416
You've been way too tired lately.

903
01:05:15,500 --> 01:05:17,333
You desperately need sleep.

904
01:05:17,416 --> 01:05:19,333
Go to bed early tonight, huh?

905
01:05:29,291 --> 01:05:30,208
[coughs]

906
01:05:32,708 --> 01:05:34,166
-What are you doing?
-Mm?

907
01:05:34,958 --> 01:05:35,791
Uh…

908
01:05:44,583 --> 01:05:46,083
I wanna sleep alone tonight.

909
01:05:47,541 --> 01:05:48,458
[chuckles]

910
01:05:49,250 --> 01:05:50,291
Okay.

911
01:05:50,375 --> 01:05:51,666
No problem, I understand.

912
01:05:52,416 --> 01:05:55,208
Get some rest.
We'll pick this up tomorrow.

913
01:06:00,083 --> 01:06:03,166
[suspenseful music]

914
01:06:45,375 --> 01:06:46,375
[thunder roars]

915
01:07:06,666 --> 01:07:09,583
[tense music]

916
01:07:11,791 --> 01:07:14,333
[gasping]

917
01:07:22,791 --> 01:07:23,750
[groans]

918
01:07:28,875 --> 01:07:31,250
[grunting]

919
01:07:34,625 --> 01:07:37,625
[mysterious music playing]

920
01:07:38,458 --> 01:07:39,958
[groans]

921
01:07:41,333 --> 01:07:42,541
[laughing]

922
01:07:47,875 --> 01:07:49,416
[laughing continues]

923
01:07:52,541 --> 01:07:54,333
[Qiang] If you wanna wake up,

924
01:07:54,416 --> 01:07:55,375
just say,

925
01:07:55,458 --> 01:07:56,875
"I'm only dreaming."

926
01:07:56,958 --> 01:07:59,125
I'm only dreaming!

927
01:08:09,875 --> 01:08:10,833
[grunts]

928
01:08:11,625 --> 01:08:12,833
[groans]

929
01:08:23,541 --> 01:08:25,125
[tires screech]

930
01:08:25,208 --> 01:08:26,041
[groans]

931
01:08:26,125 --> 01:08:27,458
[Sang Yu] Hey! Hey!

932
01:08:27,541 --> 01:08:28,708
What are you doing?

933
01:08:32,458 --> 01:08:35,500
[tense music]

934
01:08:42,875 --> 01:08:43,708
[hawks]

935
01:08:45,541 --> 01:08:46,500
[sighs]

936
01:08:58,500 --> 01:08:59,958
Stop fucking around, man.

937
01:09:00,791 --> 01:09:02,125
I have important things to do.

938
01:09:02,208 --> 01:09:04,166
You've been doing pretty well, huh?

939
01:09:04,875 --> 01:09:06,000
You're a famous guy.

940
01:09:06,083 --> 01:09:07,958
You don't need pawn shops anymore.

941
01:09:09,625 --> 01:09:11,458
Why don't we just go straight to it,
shall we?

942
01:09:12,833 --> 01:09:14,375
How much do you want from me?

943
01:09:14,458 --> 01:09:15,750
Five million.

944
01:09:15,833 --> 01:09:17,041
I'll make a call.

945
01:09:17,125 --> 01:09:19,083
[Qiang] So, now,
you're bargaining for me, huh?

946
01:09:19,666 --> 01:09:20,958
Mr. Qiang.

947
01:09:21,041 --> 01:09:22,291
Mr. Qiang.

948
01:09:22,375 --> 01:09:23,208
[grunts]

949
01:09:23,291 --> 01:09:24,458
Hey, I was only… Hey!

950
01:09:25,583 --> 01:09:27,583
I wonder how much do you think
you're worth?

951
01:09:28,333 --> 01:09:29,791
Give me a price.

952
01:09:31,291 --> 01:09:32,416
I'll give you…

953
01:09:33,208 --> 01:09:34,125
ten million Yuan.

954
01:09:36,333 --> 01:09:37,458
That in cash?

955
01:09:38,583 --> 01:09:40,125
Give him the phone.

956
01:09:53,625 --> 01:09:56,250
[motorcycle approaching]

957
01:10:01,541 --> 01:10:03,375
[tires screech]

958
01:10:06,666 --> 01:10:08,250
-Where is he?
-[man] Where is the money?

959
01:10:08,333 --> 01:10:09,958
Yeah. Why don't you tell me where he--

960
01:10:14,916 --> 01:10:16,208
Where is he?

961
01:10:20,083 --> 01:10:21,208
Just so you know,

962
01:10:21,916 --> 01:10:23,916
I'm not really part of any of this.

963
01:10:24,000 --> 01:10:27,833
I'm just delivering
as a favor to a very good friend of mine.

964
01:10:29,125 --> 01:10:32,333
The family was really pretty insisting
that I'd see the hostage

965
01:10:32,416 --> 01:10:33,833
before you get the cash.

966
01:10:33,916 --> 01:10:37,666
So, if you take the money without
my confirming my friend's safety, I mean…

967
01:10:37,750 --> 01:10:40,166
don't you think
that would be kinda bad manners?

968
01:10:40,833 --> 01:10:41,666
[grunts]

969
01:10:45,666 --> 01:10:46,500
Who is Hua'er?

970
01:10:47,250 --> 01:10:48,416
Your little girlfriend?

971
01:10:49,375 --> 01:10:50,208
Give it back.

972
01:10:54,791 --> 01:10:56,833
[Qiang] I underestimated you.

973
01:10:56,916 --> 01:10:59,000
No wonder you're so full of yourself.

974
01:10:59,083 --> 01:11:02,083
A million, ten million, a hundred million…

975
01:11:02,166 --> 01:11:05,833
In your savings alone,
you have three hundred million.

976
01:11:05,916 --> 01:11:07,250
What exactly do you do?

977
01:11:09,291 --> 01:11:10,500
You know what I think?

978
01:11:10,583 --> 01:11:12,250
I think I asked for too little.

979
01:11:12,333 --> 01:11:13,333
Qiang.

980
01:11:14,833 --> 01:11:16,458
There's something bad happening to me.

981
01:11:18,125 --> 01:11:19,250
I won't be alive for long.

982
01:11:19,333 --> 01:11:22,000
Take the money, just let us go.

983
01:11:22,083 --> 01:11:23,958
Let me take care of one last thing.

984
01:11:24,041 --> 01:11:24,875
You can do that.

985
01:11:31,458 --> 01:11:32,458
[groaning]

986
01:11:32,541 --> 01:11:33,708
What's going on?

987
01:11:34,583 --> 01:11:35,541
Sang Yu.

988
01:11:36,083 --> 01:11:37,083
You all right?

989
01:11:37,166 --> 01:11:38,750
What did these fuckers do to you?

990
01:11:38,833 --> 01:11:41,708
Do you have any idea who this is?
Oh, you'll regret this.

991
01:11:41,791 --> 01:11:44,291
Wait and see what's gonna happen.
Talking to you, mother--

992
01:11:45,250 --> 01:11:46,083
[body thuds]

993
01:11:46,166 --> 01:11:48,500
[pants]

994
01:11:48,583 --> 01:11:49,875
San? San?

995
01:11:49,958 --> 01:11:51,875
All of your businesses and home.

996
01:11:51,958 --> 01:11:53,875
Let's check out this guy's place.

997
01:11:53,958 --> 01:11:56,958
[suspenseful music]

998
01:11:57,916 --> 01:11:59,958
Hey, hello, Mr. Sang.

999
01:12:00,500 --> 01:12:02,208
[chuckles] Oh, you're back early.

1000
01:12:08,500 --> 01:12:09,541
Is that Mr. San?

1001
01:12:11,333 --> 01:12:12,875
What happened to him, huh?

1002
01:12:14,041 --> 01:12:17,000
-He's drunk.
-Oh, he's just drunk. [chuckles]

1003
01:12:17,083 --> 01:12:18,000
Delivery.

1004
01:12:19,750 --> 01:12:21,041
[elevator chimes]

1005
01:12:24,083 --> 01:12:27,083
[suspenseful music playing]

1006
01:12:34,750 --> 01:12:36,916
You already made a good life up here.

1007
01:12:37,875 --> 01:12:39,166
This can't be right.

1008
01:12:40,333 --> 01:12:41,458
I don't buy it, Qiang.

1009
01:12:41,541 --> 01:12:43,791
There should be
way more merchandise in here.

1010
01:12:49,083 --> 01:12:51,208
You can show yourself out when you finish.

1011
01:12:51,708 --> 01:12:54,708
No problem. Maybe you can just
call the owner, he can come get it.

1012
01:12:59,583 --> 01:13:02,333
[intense music plays]

1013
01:13:19,125 --> 01:13:20,166
[sniffles]

1014
01:13:26,583 --> 01:13:28,208
[groaning]

1015
01:13:29,791 --> 01:13:31,708
[grunting]

1016
01:13:31,791 --> 01:13:34,291
-[squelching]
-[continues groaning]

1017
01:13:41,541 --> 01:13:42,541
[grunts]

1018
01:13:42,625 --> 01:13:45,166
Where the hell did you get
all of these from?

1019
01:13:48,625 --> 01:13:50,000
I traded my life for it.

1020
01:13:50,083 --> 01:13:52,083
Who hasn't traded their life for money?

1021
01:13:53,000 --> 01:13:54,666
Why is yours worth so much, huh?

1022
01:13:58,750 --> 01:13:59,625
[claps]

1023
01:13:59,708 --> 01:14:03,708
[Qiang] Hey, hey. Put that down.
Don't move anything.

1024
01:14:03,791 --> 01:14:04,958
[Sang Yu] It's all right.

1025
01:14:05,041 --> 01:14:07,291
You can take all of it. It's okay.

1026
01:14:07,375 --> 01:14:08,833
I won't call the cops.

1027
01:14:09,833 --> 01:14:11,125
But if you kill me,

1028
01:14:12,375 --> 01:14:13,416
you're in for it.

1029
01:14:15,000 --> 01:14:19,166
A time thief can steal so much
he could provide for the rest of his life.

1030
01:14:19,791 --> 01:14:20,833
And yet,

1031
01:14:21,416 --> 01:14:22,750
he's always a thief.

1032
01:14:22,833 --> 01:14:25,083
Who lies to himself
and betrays what he is.

1033
01:14:26,250 --> 01:14:28,458
He'll never control his own destiny.

1034
01:14:30,208 --> 01:14:31,208
[receptionist] Mr. Sang.

1035
01:14:32,833 --> 01:14:34,208
Mr. Sang, are you there?

1036
01:14:36,041 --> 01:14:38,000
Mr. Sang, are you okay?

1037
01:14:41,333 --> 01:14:43,208
-[beeps]
-[Sang Yu] What's the matter?

1038
01:14:43,291 --> 01:14:46,666
[receptionist] Mr. Sang, you have a guest.
She said her name is Hua'er.

1039
01:14:46,750 --> 01:14:48,333
-Should I let her up?
-Say I'm not here.

1040
01:14:48,416 --> 01:14:49,916
-Tell her to come later.
-Sang Yu?

1041
01:14:50,625 --> 01:14:52,958
Why can't you tell me
what you're hiding from?

1042
01:14:53,750 --> 01:14:55,458
I'm hiding from you! Get out!

1043
01:14:55,541 --> 01:14:57,083
Leave now!

1044
01:14:58,500 --> 01:15:00,166
Is something going on up there?

1045
01:15:00,250 --> 01:15:02,833
[receptionist] Mr. Sang,
I think you should let her come up.

1046
01:15:02,916 --> 01:15:04,791
-You can explain--
-Quiet!

1047
01:15:05,958 --> 01:15:07,916
Do you remember what you said to me?

1048
01:15:08,000 --> 01:15:10,458
How you can dump
three guys like me in a year?

1049
01:15:10,541 --> 01:15:12,250
You can add me to that list today.

1050
01:15:12,875 --> 01:15:14,791
[inhales deeply]

1051
01:15:14,875 --> 01:15:16,000
You know what I think?

1052
01:15:17,666 --> 01:15:20,208
I think this isn't about some regret
in your past.

1053
01:15:20,291 --> 01:15:23,083
[somber music]

1054
01:15:26,875 --> 01:15:28,416
Hang on, Ma'am.

1055
01:15:29,125 --> 01:15:31,000
He just opened the door.

1056
01:15:33,125 --> 01:15:34,333
[elevator dings]

1057
01:15:44,291 --> 01:15:46,375
Don't move! I'll snap you to death!

1058
01:15:50,833 --> 01:15:54,000
[tense music playing]

1059
01:15:55,375 --> 01:15:56,375
[Hua'er] Sang Yu.

1060
01:15:57,166 --> 01:15:58,625
Are you there, Sang Yu?

1061
01:15:59,875 --> 01:16:01,083
Are you okay?

1062
01:16:01,750 --> 01:16:02,958
Please, Sang Yu…

1063
01:16:03,583 --> 01:16:04,500
Wait, stop!

1064
01:16:05,291 --> 01:16:06,708
If you take that off, you'll die.

1065
01:16:08,541 --> 01:16:10,125
[Qiang] Young lovers.

1066
01:16:10,208 --> 01:16:12,875
What good is money
without a girl to go with it?

1067
01:16:12,958 --> 01:16:14,166
[Hua'er] Who are you people?

1068
01:16:14,250 --> 01:16:15,541
What do you want?

1069
01:16:15,625 --> 01:16:17,166
You want money, right?

1070
01:16:17,250 --> 01:16:19,916
I have a café, it's worth some money.
You can have it.

1071
01:16:20,958 --> 01:16:22,041
[both gasp]

1072
01:16:22,125 --> 01:16:23,458
-Hua'er…
-[Hua'er] Sang Yu…

1073
01:16:23,541 --> 01:16:24,625
[gasps]

1074
01:16:26,458 --> 01:16:28,208
Don't touch her! Get away from her!

1075
01:16:28,291 --> 01:16:30,166
-Don't you dare!
-[Hua'er] Sang Yu…

1076
01:16:30,250 --> 01:16:31,333
[grunts]

1077
01:16:34,083 --> 01:16:36,125
Qiang. Qiang. Qiang.

1078
01:16:36,958 --> 01:16:38,125
Qiang, I was wrong.

1079
01:16:38,208 --> 01:16:41,166
Please, just let her go.
You can take whatever you want.

1080
01:16:41,250 --> 01:16:44,458
I have more stuff.
I promise, there's more. Don't do it.

1081
01:16:45,166 --> 01:16:46,375
I'm begging you.

1082
01:16:52,208 --> 01:16:53,250
[inhales sharply]

1083
01:16:59,458 --> 01:17:00,458
[Hua'er] Sang Yu.

1084
